      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/47/964",
      "text": [
        " «إِنْ كُنْتَ عَلَى وُضُوءٍ فَأَنْتَ مُعَقِّبٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.964 - Hisham ibn Salim said to Abu Abdullah (as):\n\"I go out and I love to be in a state of spiritual continuation (mu'aqqib).\"\nImam (as) replied: \"If you are in a state of ablution (wudhu), then you are considered to be in a state of spiritual continuation (mu'aqqib).\""
        ]
      }
    },
